data.CNOTES:
Dear Greta Thunberg,

The voice you have shown for future generations in your climate campaign is nothing short of the caffeine the world so desperately needed to awaken from their deep slumber.

I have been deeply affected by your inspiring and fierce words.

I am a 29 year old law graduate from Switzerland living in Melbourne Australia. Intergenerational equity is a term I learned at law school whilst studying energy production as a major. 

What you are fighting for, is exactly that. Equity for future generations.
You are holding accountable those who are perpetrating against our futures.
I would love to join your ranks in resolving the climate war peacefully.

Moving towards a complete transparency political system is now needed for their future accountability. Using the internet as a tool for holding politicians in our faded democracy accountable for their actions is the only way to resolve this permanently. Injustices occur in many different ways. Climate is one that threatens the very fibre of our existence. More injustices will come to pass if moving towards complete transparency isn’t aimed for.

I fight for the rights of refugees, my friend fights for the rights of women, another fights for the rights of homosexuality and so on and so forth. We fight to live on in this world but in what conditions? Fighting for the environment we exist in needs to be the prelude to our symphony of change.

You have mobilised a large crowd, I pray you continue your work in the noble pursuit well into your adulthood and I hope I get to be a part of it.

Sincerest respects,

Victor Aeberli
(A law student with a view for change and not the silver kind…)

Hi there! 
I'm Barbara, I represent a Contemporary Dance Company here in Brazil, called Núcleo Contemporâneo Eliane Fetzer. We are a group of artists, that want to do much more than just dance. We want to use our  art to help and support causes. And so, our newest work, called "Para Onde Foram as Andorinhas" (Where Did the Swallows go), brings a report about all that's been rappening about the fires in Amazonia, the climate changes, the death of indigenous people and animals that live on the forests, among other important things. We want and need this to be more than just a show for entertainment, and become a way to aware more people about the subject.

data.CNOTES:
We demand urgent action. Help us by supporting and joining the millions across the globe taking action and bringing awareness to our ongoing climate crisis. We want Sakskatchewan to be apart of the bigger conversation about what we can do too. We as a unified community wish to bring awareness to our rising global crisis through a peaceful climate demonstration in front of the La Ronge Town Hall slotted on Friday October 11th, 2019 at 12:00 PM – 3 PM.

People across the globe are experiencing its effects. Intense rainstorms, severe droughts, extreme heat waves, flooding, the destruction of homes, communities, natural spaces etc. Even the most vulnerable to these effects are among us: our children, our elders and the less fortunate. They are all in danger of increasing cold, heat stress and pollution. Yet, we avert our eyes. Because well…it isn’t affecting us too much? Wrong. The effects of climate change are very real, and this is even happening in our own backyard. Fires, flooding, insane windstorms, intense weather that have been ongoing the past few years. None like we’ve ever seen before, yet it’ll only get worse if we say and do nothing. We need to stop averting our eyes and face what is happening, even in remote communities. 

What do we want to do about it? We want to take a stance and bring awareness to the world and humanity’s biggest threat. From our government we want to demand action. We want to demand reform for its criminal inaction on our ecological crisis. We want to ask for honesty, responsibility and courage to face our climate crisis head-on. We want to plead with our leaders to stop basing decisions on economic growth and take immediate action by listening to the climate and biodiversity data accumulated over the last 30 years. Plead to pay attention now, before it’s too late. 

On a community-level we want to start a conversation about what we can do. Introducing the idea of cracking down on pollutants in our community with the usage of cleaner energy. Introducing more local farming and supporting the food banks and schools in their effort for a cleaner community through their gardens, stricter regulations on pollution. also seeking the support of local businesses to follow in the footsteps of businesses taking more sustainable routes such as Cravings etc. 

We no longer want to sit around and wait for slow change, we as students want to step up against this bystander effect circulating and this ignored crisis. Climate change is affecting our community, our future, your children’s children and so much more. We want to ask for change now before it’s too late. As a unified group of people, we want to make a difference by bringing awareness, inspire deeper discussion about what we can change. Show people that change can come from the will of the people, our citizens.

Very fascinated with AI and interested in Innovative technologies and tools like high-performance computing, deep learning, machine learning, inference, visualization, smart cities, medical imaging, and IoT. I have a wide array of knowledge from experimenting AI solutions for specific expert systems like predicting stocks, generating images, reconstructing images, sentiment analysis, lung detection illnesses, making smart solutions for Smart Cities like smart parking, anomaly detection and more between a few. IntelliScan a project in which I'm particularly proud of that uses transfer learning for training a model, that to my surprise was with a rather small data set form Keggle. On the other hand, I've demonstrated the ability to convey technical topics to clients and have been recognized for my exemplary record of accomplishment to establish and maintain productive work environments and relationships.
Smart Cities are key to Humanity as a whole. Today the thought of creating True Ai is not a question of "if" but of "when". This is because technology and understanding of the brain are evolving so rapidly. together these developments will enable us to create computers that can think and learn independently. It's pretty hard to predict the future that awaits us with 100% accuracy at least based on observation of trends and technology today we could make predictions for tomorrow take Moore's law for example. especially with GPUs, graphene processors, and quantum gates are around the corner. some more than others... Yes. Smart Cities are an excellent way to unleash the true power of AI and impact humanity just like the discovery of fire impacted our ancestors. I like to think about this era like the "The Fourth Age" or "Life 3.0". Without a doubt, the future is in our hands and we must strive for progress if we want to persist throughout time

In the future, I see myself able to oversee mayor software developments to make an impact of the usage of uprising technologies especially Artificial intelligence, essentially upgrading humanity as we know it. Eventually, the adoption of these new technologies in today's digital transformation will not only be a matter of life or death for the big enterprises but for all humanity and the Planet.

Denmark klokken 10:00(cirka) den 6 december du kan hjemmefra lave skilte og bandet hvor der står ting omkring klimaet osv håber vi ses den 6 december😊|THE OFFICIAL NEW YEAR'S DECLARATION OF A CLIMATE EMERGENCY FOR THE PLANET

On this day, the 31st of December 2019, we solemny declare a STATE OF CLIMATE EMERGENCY for the planet and all life on it, including humanity. The Declaration we are making is based on indisputable scienctific evidence - that a climate crisis exists and that this crisis is predominantly man made. And, as such, it is our duty to acknowledge this fact through the declaration of a Climate Emergency.

The purpose and aim of the Declaration is threefold.
1 - First of all, to acknowledge humanity's direct role in the present climate crisis, through the expulsion of carbon emissions into the atmosphere from industry, trade and pollutants from public and private vehicles. It is estimated that the world uses 100 million barrels of oil each day and the CO2 created from this consumption has severely damaged the environment, triggering the present phenomenon of global-warming. As informed responsible individuals, we refute the theory that global warming is a natural phenomenon and hold fast to the scientific evidence that global warming is predominantly man made.
2 - By making this Declaration we aim to inform the general public about ALL the relevant scientific facts pertaining to the severity of this crisis, and that we only have a very limited time before 'tipping points' are reached and permanent damage is done to the planet and ourselves. It is estimated by the IPCC (the Intergovernmental Panel for Climate Change) that this tipping point is 1.5 C degrees rise in the Earth's temperature. The IPCC also estimates that, with our present rate of CO2 emmissions, we will probably reach this point in or around 2030. If this occurs, inestimable and probably irreversible damage will be done to the planet and all life on it.
3 - Faced with possibly the greatest crisis that humanity has experienced in its history, it will be necessary for us to look for very innovative and even unorthodox solutions to this problem. We have to face the fact that not only have our governments failed, but also ourselves, along with the values and institutions of our society. It is now necessary to radically reform and update these values and institutions and come up with a new system of democracy, where elected politicians and legislative bodies have to be kept in check by independent, non politiclaly affilated advisory committees. Our present democratic system has proved totally incapable of curbing the greed and corruption of big business, and putting the people's and the planet's interests before their own. As part of this Declaration, we demand that a new system of govenment be implemented - one that runs along the lines of cooperation and consensus between elected representatives and advisory bodies composed of scientific experts, envrionmental activists and other informed and dedicated members of the public.

Originally as Nature Walkers India, AWARA walker-runner-volunteers cleared hundreds of tonnes of trash dumped on the river bed & carved a nature trail along that trained scores of middle & long distance runners, marathoners, some from slumkids & others from deprived backgrounds.  Such activity spurned away hordes of open defecators, waste dumpers, sand-miners, drug peddlars, vandals & other criminal elements off the river precinct.

If possible i'll do my best|People worldwide are set to participate in the climate strike. Those who are kids now, will be the most affected from the Climate Emergency in the next 20 years. In the next 40 years there may not be an inhabitable planets if we don't act NOW.

The Mumbai Chapter of Fridays For Future (India), with the help of public volunteers as young as 7 years old are going to demonstrate peacefully.

We meet near Hotel Ramada, Juhu at 3.10 pm IST. We plan to meet all safety regulations and permissions by adult volunteers, media and local authorities till 4:30pm. With protection to youngsters and after making arrangements for safe returns of everyone, we gather with our  signboards, placards, cardboards, drawings and writeups, memes, cartoons at Juhu Beach Entrance 1at 5 pm on 24 May 2019. Then we all move upto Birla Lane, while peacefully educating the public and showing our support for the Climate Activist and 2019 Nobel Prize Nominated Greta Thunberg for the causes of climate action, declaring climate emergency, urging those who can act now.

We welcome all.

We will make this fun and enjoyable while we display no anger or resentment.

All the people in power, government,  teachers, students, general public is welcome.

Please read about our cause and if you can bring anything poster that is funny and conveys our message for saving the planet earth from climate energency.

Remember, there's no planet B.

We also welcome everyone to listen to Adv. Girish Raut, a well known environment activist during the event.

Please help others during the event, and be nice to those who are around you.|Globle warming and climate change !

data.CNOTES: I am the cofounder and outreach director for WinWisely (WinWisely.org and WinWisely on Facebook). We are to our knowledge the first and only app whose mission is be able to recruit and commit larger numbers of volunteers than ever before willing to do direct action to keep fossil fuels in the ground in the USA, specifically 1 M Americans, and 2-3M more to support them as well as pressure Congress to rapidly pass a robustly funded Green New Deal. See or demo packet at bit.ly/WinWiselyPrep (a 3min animation plus 10min video). Think: Behavior economics + kickstarter +peerbonding meets movement building. We urgently need funding connector help, another programer (ideally two), researcher, and user tester. I can be reached at Gary@WinWisely.org. I am at the moment living in Oaxaca, to be able to afford to fund this so far from my own savings. Here are what more than 20 top organizers and IT pros have to say about us: Bit.ly/WinWiselyReviews. My prior startup, CoupleWise, to help committed relationships succeed, is now taking off.

data.CNOTES:
From the perspective of out-of-the-box thinkers, innovators and doers, we want to contribute a small video series. Its goal is to change today’s painfully slow progress by decision makers into one able to meet the deadlines set by nature. 

Today and exceptions granted, a gridlocked system prevents urgently needed, innovative solutions from being seen and implement. It appears, the higher the potential value, the quicker such solutions get stuck. The video series identifies root causes and solutions. In video 4, Prof. Michael Fitzgerald answers this question: What would Einstein, Newton and Darwin do? It differs from how things are addressed today. In video 5, a simple, yet high-speed innovation track for high(est) impact innovations is created.

As we are out-of-the-box thinkers, innovators and doers, this contribution got stuck in the gridlocked system. The only option left to get this system fixed is with the help of Fridays For Future. Hence, we would appreciate if this would be added as weekly online event to Global Strike for Future activities. What we have just done as well is to suggest the video series to Fridays For Future ‘Videos for World Improvers’ (suggest@fridaysforfuture.org). 

If you want to have a look ahead of them going public, here are the links:  

1.	From Painfully Slow Progress to a Drastic Acceleration [1:58m] https://youtu.be/HqIHzhGCtgg
Corona has shown that decision makers can change very quick!

2.	What Would Einstein Do Next? [3:55m] https://youtu.be/yGKi-9eL0YQ
And: How people can learn to adapt to his guidance.

3.	We Need a Slogan [5:50m] https://youtu.be/Nv95PnrJH-A
To get people in the overload of conflicting information on the same page, such a slogan needs to provide a common direction. A proposal is made.

4.	What would Einstein, Newton and Darwin Do? [20:20m] https://youtu.be/EWA93HX5xwU
Interview with Prof. Michael Fitzgerald.
The practices of great innovators differ from those applied today. It includes recommendation to unlock high(est)-impact innovations missed today. 

5.	Creating a High-Speed Innovation Track for High-Impact Innovations [7:45m] https://youtu.be/H6mSRQWVBg4
It provides root causes through which available solutions of high(est) impact are missed (!) and how this can be solved the easy way. 

6.	How Root Causes and Solutions Can Be Found (under development)

Questions? Clarification needs? Don’t hesitate to contact me.

Dette holder ikke mål! Norge må slutte å skape en brennende verden!

data.CNOTES:
Red Rocks Initiatives for Sustainable Development received two prestigious awards which recommend its vision to be a leading player in integrating tourism, conservation and sustainable community development in the wider Virunga massif. The awards including one from Rwanda Tourism Chamber recognized Red Rocks as the best community based initiative while another one from Madrid, Spain being a recognition from UNWTO in collaboration with CASA Africa and Fitur as an organization that is integrating tourism, conservation and sustainable community development.

To achieve this, the local people are encouraged and facilitated to take part in activities which bring them positive impact, particularly uplifting their living standards. This encourages them to have motivation to help in environmental conservation and they also provides sustainable development talks to travelers who would wish to make positive impacts to local communities in different areas like foreign language and new skills acquisition, women and youth empowerment programs, and conservation and community development among others.

 We have enabled efforts to popularize cultural values, to develop the diversity of production and to safeguard our rich cultural heritage. The projects are now inspirational for sustainable rural development through socially –beneficial initiatives. When visiting Musanze, you are welcome to come and visit for a day to check out the initiative’s programs and make a difference supporting our activities in different ways.|Red Rocks Initiatives for Sustainable Development is a non-profit organization operating in Africa. We work with individuals and groups to encourage, support, and celebrate more sustainable actions. From creating awareness of Global warming crisis, ending the use of plastic seed bags, preserving our natural resources and cultural heritage with the purpose of promoting tourism and environmental conservation as the leading sustainable community empowerment tool to uplift the socio economic status of the locals. Our organization does not only provide an opportunity for travelers to volunteer in Africa ’s most coveted destinations but also provides invaluable research opportunities for academia which include fellowship placements with sustainable-focused projects  across Africa , providing opportunities for hands-on learning and service. Our educational trips for students and young professionals make them learn about critical environmental issues and they contribute to create solutions across Africa. We welcome everyone to join and share their actions working together to increase examples of well-managed sustainable tourism and environmental conservation to uplift Africans out of poverty and instill them a sense of purpose and pride.

Like the prayers on the Tibetan flags they become blessings upon contact with the sun and the air, to spread over people and infinite space, write these words of peace, love, health, light, gratitude in water ... with the feeling of enhancing the noble virtues of human beings and offering in their evaporation, the awakening of everything we have to become aware to heal the Earth, our only home.
In union with the fridaysforfuture movement
María Eugenia Manrique, artist and calligrapher at the city of Barcelona Spain

Acción de arte efímero - Palabras para la Tierra… 
Al igual que las oraciones en las banderas tibetanas se transforman en bendiciones al contacto con el sol y el aire, para esparcirse sobre las personas en el espacio infinito, escribo en agua estas palabras de paz, amor, salud, luz, gratitud… con el sentimiento de potenciar las nobles virtudes de los seres humanos y ofrecer en su evaporación, el despertar de todo aquello que hemos de tomar conciencia para sanar la Tierra, nuestro único hogar...
En unión con el movimiento fridaysforfuture 
María Eugenia Manrique, artista y calígrafa en la ciudad de Barcelona|Love is the answer|Go Vegan!|THE LAST DAY OF THE COP . We need to claim CHANGES , ACTIONS. This COP would be useful

data.CNOTES: We will be hosting a cleaning action across the Congost river course along Granollers town, in collaboration with two Schools (Joan Solà & Ferrer i Guàrdia) the goal is to let the kids be aware of the growing problem of plastic pollution. They are preparing an Opera that talks about Climate Change, and with this Friday Action the teachers and us we want them to be an active part of the movement. As the Capital City, Granollers is a big town with many pollution problems due to it's surrounding industry, and non responsible people behavior. The kids need a voice and we want to give it to them by opening their eyes.

data.CNOTES:
I’m Manel Kenani. I’m 11 years old. I’m from Kairouan, Tunisia and I’m enrolled in sixth primary school. My school is El Fateh.  My school participates to the global action for climate. Kairouan is the harvest town in Tunisia. The temperature normally reaches over 48 degrees Celsius during the summer. The life, in this period of the year, is very hard. The children can’t play outside, they haven’t any place to go, no swimming pools, no forests, no sea or rivers. Inside is very hot and we can’t concentrate in studying or reading. Only a little bit of the population has air conditioners but we know this is not the good solution.
 These extremes conditions are the consequences of the climate changing and the rising temperature. We suffer also the water cuts and the trees privation.
The North Africa is one of the regions of the globe more vulnerable in consequence of climate changing.
For these reasons I’ve decided to reach the global strike and to ask the politicians to stop the fossils fuels and to work for the forestation, …

data.CNOTES:
Rockwool’s proposed factory in Ranson, WV would be a climate disaster- the kind of facility that should no longer be built anywhere if we want to preserve our climate for future generations!  
The plant would burn around 90 tons of coal and 1.6 million cubic feet of fracked gas per day.  It would emit 156 thousand tons of harmful pollutants per year.  The site is located just across the road from a Title 1 elementary school.  
In spite of this, Rockwool, the Danish insulation manufacturer, claims to be a “Green” company.  
Please join me and Eastern Panhandle Green Coalition every Friday as we peacefully protest this company near the entrance to the site.  The location is at the intersection of Northport Avenue and the Route 9 Bike Path, in Ranson, WV.  
We will gather from 11am till 1pm, starting on January 17th, 2020 and continuing until Rockwool agrees to either leave or go Zero Emissions at its factory.

data.CNOTES:
Am Nakabuye Hilda Flavia, the youth mobilizer at Fridays For Future - Uganda, a student and youth led activist group and part of the global movement of youth striking for Climate. We are supported by Green Campaign Africa and act as a ground for students, youth and the community to participate in Climate Strikes.|The FridaysForFuture climate strike in Uganda will be led by FridaysForFuture-Uganda in the City of Wakiso a ditrict few meters from Kampala City. Prticipation will attract over 1000+ students fron 4 high schools and youth from 3 Universities. We shall be joined by the All Wakiso District local government staff, the Wakiso, Farmers Association and the general public. 
Prior to the strike will be the Cimate Strike Artwork Day that will be on Thursday 19th, at the Wakiso District Council/Community Hall. We are glad to inform you that the Swedish Embsassy of Kampala is in full support of all strike artwork materials that will cater for the planned 1000+ strikers and the joining groups from the public.

data.CNOTES:
Am Nirere Sadrach, the Coordinator of Fridays For Future, I am registering this strike on behalf of the Team of Organizers and other climate strikers. The movement is growing and we are looking forward to having over 1000 people striking in Areas of Kampala, Entebbe and Jinja town, involvement will be mainly from both high school and university students. We have also catered for public to participate more so young people and over 2 youth groups have been mobilized to join students for strike.  We shall give you all the deatils as they happen.
